news.title: Vaishnavi Group to redevelop Bengaluru's Chalukya Hotel into grade-A office
news.para: Redevelopment of the property, which is owned by Mohammed Iqbal, is expected to take two years from the time the requisite approvals are in. It will offer 150,000 sq. ft. of office space, the people cited earlier said.

news.title: Ozone Group to restructure loan by selling commercial, residential assets
news.para: The Bengaluru-headquartered firm, which has over Rs 4,000 crore debt on its books, is in talks with developers and investors to sell its assets and pare its debt.

news.title: Over 200 buildings in Uttar Pradesh are without fire NOC, suggests data
news.para: The data suggests that these buildings do not have the mandatory no objection certificate (NOC) from the fire safety department.

news.title: Blending biomass pellets with coal not trending in Punjab brick industry
news.para: The board has lost the hope of convincing the brick industry this year. All it meetings with the brick-kiln owners were fruitless.

news.title: Pune: 7,783 illegal structures found in PMRDA limits; FIRs against 94
news.para: PMRDA commissioner Rahul Mahiwal said the illegal structures have come up over the last eight years. "An action plan has been readied in this regard and we will carry it out immediately," he said.

news.title: Guwahati civic body to hold three-day camps in all wards to collect property tax
news.para: According to the authorities, about 40% of the three lakh households do not pay property taxes despite offline and online facilities to do so. The city residents can pay property tax either by visiting the GMC office or online.

news.title: Tax not paid, 12 commercial buildings in Chandigarh get sealing notice
news.para: The Chandigarh municipal corporation had sealed four such commercial buildings, located in the Centra Mall in Industrial Area, a few days back.

news.title: Puravankara posts Rs 17.22 crore net loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 252.85 crore in Q2 FY23, a dip of 7.36 per cent from Rs 272.95 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: MahaRERA irregularities in Kalyan-Dombivli: SIT arrests five persons
news.para: ​Those arrested are agents operating real estate businesses and obtaining registration of projects, Senior Inspector Vikas Ghodke of Unit V of the Crime Branch, currently attached to the SIT, said.

news.title: DCB Bank raises MCLR rates across tenors by 27 bps
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR rate will be priced at 10.23 per cent from Saturday against the existing rate of 9.96 per cent.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC Green View buyers want FIR against developer
news.para: Earlier this year, the homebuyers had filed a complaint against the developer with the economic offences wing (EoW) of Delhi Police, which transferred the case to Gurgaon police in May.

news.title: YEIDA receives roadmap from Jaiprakash Associates to clear dues
news.para: The development authority had on February 12, 2020 cancelled the allotment of 1,000 hectares over non-payment of lease rent, premium and interest, together amounting to Rs 900 crore.

news.title: Greater Noida development body to hold builder-wise registry camps
news.para: They added that after getting positive responses from weekly camps held last month, the authority has issued a roaster for facilitating the registry of flats for November.

news.title: Geberit's operating profit fell 26.4% in Q3 2022
news.para: The maker of bathroom piping, ceramics and shower toilets said its sales fell to 790.7 million Swiss francs ($788.33 million)during the three months to the end of September.

news.title: Runwise raises $19 million to improve buildings' energy efficiency
news.para: The Series A financing was also backed by several large real estate owners, including New York's Rudin and SOJA Ventures, the investment arm of the Swig family that owns Halstead and Brown Harris Stevens.
